In this course the topics include: the concept of advertising and psychological nature of advertising influence; main mechanisms of advertising effects; core elements of advertising messages and their structure; basic concepts and principles of persuasion; categories of advertising and their specific features.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of this course is to teach basic knowledge of advertising psychology, present an introductory overview of the basic topics and concepts of advertising psychology and to help acquire the skills of analyzing advertising messages in the context of commercial advertising and propaganda.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completion of this course students: - know the position of advertising psychology among other social science disciplines and its role and capabilities in practical advertising - understand mechanisms and tricks of the trade in advertising - know basic concepts of advertising and psychology of influence - command skills of independent analysis and understanding of real advertising messages, their principal structure and ways of influence;  - carry out analysis of real advertising communications.
